{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-awesome-all-timeline-js","path":"/2017/11/28/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Track Awesome List"}},"allAwesomeItem":{"nodes":[{"awesomeListRepo":"sindresorhus/awesome-electron","categoryHTML":"<h2>Apps</h2><h3>Samples</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://electronjs.org/blog/simple-samples#activity-monitor\">Activity Monitor</a> - Shows a doughnut chart of the CPU system, user, and idle activity time.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T22:50:33.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"sindresorhus/awesome-electron","categoryHTML":"<h2>Apps</h2><h3>Samples</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://electronjs.org/blog/simple-samples#hash\">Hash</a> - Shows the hash values of entered text using different algorithms.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T22:50:33.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"sindresorhus/awesome-electron","categoryHTML":"<h2>Apps</h2><h3>Samples</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://electronjs.org/blog/simple-samples#prices\">Prices</a> - Shows the current price of oil, gold, and silver using the Yahoo Finance API.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T22:50:33.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"sindresorhus/awesome-electron","categoryHTML":"<h2>Documentation</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://electronjs.org/docs/tutorial/quick-start\">Quick Start</a></li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T22:50:33.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"sindresorhus/awesome-electron","categoryHTML":"<h2>Documentation</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://electronjs.org/docs\">Official docs</a></li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T22:50:33.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Simple: cryptography for non-engineers</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://dspace.mit.edu/bitstream/handle/1721.1/97690/MIT-CSAIL-TR-2015-026.pdf\">Keys under Doormats</a> - Or why cryptography shouldn't be backdoored, by a all-star committee of crypto researches from around the world.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Brief introductions</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.garykessler.net/library/crypto.html\">An Overview of Cryptography</a> - By Gary C. Kessler.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Brief introductions</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://inst.eecs.berkeley.edu/~cs268/sp02/cached_papers/needham.pdf\">Using Encryption for Authentication in Large Networks</a> - By Needham, Schroeder: this is were crypto-based auth starts.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>General cryptographic interest</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://eprint.iacr.org/2004/152.pdf\">Another Look at “Provable Security”</a> - Inquiries into formalism and naive intuition behind security proofs, by Neal Koblitz et al.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Hashing</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/FIPS/NIST.FIPS.198-1.pdf\">FIPS 198-1: HMACs</a> - The Keyed-Hash Message Authentication Code FIPS document.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Hashing</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/FIPS/NIST.FIPS.202.pdf\">FIPS 202: SHA3</a> - SHA-3 Standard: Permutation-Based Hash and Extendable-Output Functions.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Hashing</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://eprint.iacr.org/2006/187.pdf\">On the Security of HMAC and NMAC Based on HAVAL, MD4, MD5, SHA-0 and SHA-1</a> - Security analysis of different legacy HMAC schemes by Jongsung Kim et al.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Hashing</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://eprint.iacr.org/2001/074\">On the Security of Randomized CBC-MAC Beyond the Birthday Paradox Limit </a> - Security of randomized CBC-MACs and a new construction that resists birthday paradox attacks and provably reaches full security, by E. Jaulmes et al.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Secret key cryptography</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://csrc.nist.gov/groups/ST/toolkit/BCM/modes_development.html\">List of proposed operation modes of AES</a> - Maintained by NIST.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Secret key cryptography</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.moserware.com/2009/09/stick-figure-guide-to-advanced.html\">Stick figure guide to AES</a> - If stuff above was a bit hard or you're looking for a good laugh.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Secret key cryptography</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://cr.yp.to/antiforgery/cachetiming-20050414.pdf\">Cache timing attacks on AES</a> - Example of designing great practical attack on cipher implementation, by Daniel J. Bernstein.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Secret key cryptography</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://cs.tau.ac.il/~tromer/papers/cache.pdf\">Cache Attacks and Countermeasures: the Case of AES</a> - Side channel attacks on AES, another view, by Dag Arne Osvik, Adi Shamir and Eran Tromer.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Secret key cryptography</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://cr.yp.to/snuffle/salsafamily-20071225.pdf\">Salsa20 family of stream ciphers</a> - Broad explanation of Salsa20 security cipher by Daniel J. Bernstein.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Secret key cryptography</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://csrc.nist.gov/csrc/media/projects/cryptographic-standards-and-guidelines/documents/aes-development/rijndael-ammended.pdf#page=1\">AES submission document on Rijndael</a> - Original Rijndael proposal by Joan Daemen and Vincent Rijmen.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Secret key cryptography</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.ecrypt.eu.org/ecrypt1/documents/D.STVL.3-2.5.pdf\">Ongoing Research Areas in Symmetric Cryptography</a> - Overview of ongoing research in secret key crypto and hashes by ECRYPT Network of Excellence in Cryptology.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Cryptoanalysis</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.ecrypt.eu.org/stream/papersdir/2007/010.pdf\">Differential Cryptanalysis of Salsa20/8</a> - A great example of stream cipher cryptoanalysis, by Yukiyasu Tsunoo et al.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Cryptoanalysis</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://eprint.iacr.org/2008/263\">Slide Attacks on a Class of Hash Functions</a> - Applying slide attacks (typical cryptoanalysis technique for block ciphers) to hash functions, M. Gorski et al.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Cryptoanalysis</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.schneier.com/academic/archives/2000/01/self-study_course_in.html\">Self-Study Course in Block Cipher Cryptanalysis</a> - Attempt to organize the existing literature of block-cipher cryptanalysis in a way that students can use to learn cryptanalytic techniques and ways to break new algorithms, by Bruce Schneier.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Cryptoanalysis</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://crypto.junod.info/phdthesis.pdf\">Statistical Cryptanalysis of Block Ciphers</a> - By Pascal Junod.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Cryptoanalysis</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.cs.technion.ac.il/users/wwwb/cgi-bin/tr-info.cgi/2006/PHD/PHD-2006-04\">Cryptoanalysis of block ciphers and protocols</a> - By Elad Pinhas Barkan.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Public key cryptography: General and DLP</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www-ee.stanford.edu/~hellman/publications/24.pdf\">New Directions in Cryptography</a> - Seminal paper by Diffie and Hellman, introducing public key cryptography and key exchange/agreement protocol.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Public key cryptography: General and DLP</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc2631\">RFC 2631: Diffie-Hellman Key Agreement</a> - An explanation of the Diffie-Hellman methon in more engineering terms.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Public key cryptography: General and DLP</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://people.csail.mit.edu/rivest/Rsapaper.pdf\">A Method for Obtaining Digital Signatures and Public-Key Cryptosystems</a> -  Original paper introducing RSA algorithm.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Public key cryptography: General and DLP</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.di-mgt.com.au/rsa_alg.html\">RSA Algorithm</a> - Rather education explanation of every bit behind RSA.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Public key cryptography: General and DLP</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.merkle.com/1974/PuzzlesAsPublished.pdf\">Secure Communications Over Insecure Channels </a> - Paper by R. Merkle,   predated \"New directions in cryptography\" though it was published after it. The Diffie-Hellman key exchange is an implementation of such a Merkle system.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Public key cryptography: General and DLP</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://crypto.stanford.edu/~dabo/papers/ssl-timing.pdf\">Remote timing attacks are practical</a> - An example in attacking practical crypto implementationby D. Boneh, D. Brumley.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Public key cryptography: General and DLP</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://eprint.iacr.org/2005/307.pdf\">The Equivalence Between the DHP and DLP for Elliptic Curves Used in Practical Applications, Revisited</a> - by K. Bentahar.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Public key cryptography: Elliptic-curve crypto</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://eprint.iacr.org/2008/390.pdf\">Elliptic Curve Cryptography: the serpentine course of a paradigm shift</a> - Historic inquiry into development of ECC and it's adoption.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Public key cryptography: Elliptic-curve crypto</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://blog.bjrn.se/2015/07/lets-construct-elliptic-curve.html\">Let's construct an elliptic curve: Introducing Crackpot2065</a> - Fine example of building up ECC from scratch.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Public key cryptography: Elliptic-curve crypto</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.hyperelliptic.org/EFD/\">Explicit-Formulas Database</a> - For many elliptic curve representation forms.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Public key cryptography: Elliptic-curve crypto</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://delta.cs.cinvestav.mx/~francisco/arith/julio.pdf\">Software implementation of the NIST elliptic curves over prime fields</a> - Pracitcal example of implementing elliptic curve crypto, by M. Brown et al.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Public key cryptography: Elliptic-curve crypto</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://ed25519.cr.yp.to/ed25519-20110926.pdf\">High-speed high-security signatures</a> - Seminal paper on EdDSA signatures on ed25519 curve by Daniel J. Bernstein et al.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Zero Knowledge Proofs</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.wisdom.weizmann.ac.il/~oded/gmw1.html\">How to construct zero-knowledge proof systems for NP</a> - Classic paper by Goldreich,  Micali and Wigderson.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Zero Knowledge Proofs</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.math.ias.edu/~avi/PUBLICATIONS/MYPAPERS/GMW86/GMW86.pdf\">Proofs that yield nothing but their validity and a Methodology of Cryptographic protocol design</a> - By Goldreich,  Micali and Wigderson, a relative to the above.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Zero Knowledge Proofs</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.mathunion.org/ICM/ICM1986.2/Main/icm1986.2.1444.1451.ocr.pdf\">How to Prove a Theorem So No One Else Can Claim It</a> - By Manuel Blum.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Zero Knowledge Proofs</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://groups.csail.mit.edu/cis/pubs/shafi/1989-siamjc.pdf\">Knowledge complexity of interactive proof systems</a> - By GoldWasser, Micali and Rackoff. Defining computational complexity of \"knowledge\" within zero knowledge proofs.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Zero Knowledge Proofs</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.austinmohr.com/work/files/zkp.pdf\">A Survey of Zero-Knowledge Proofs with Applications to Cryptography</a> - Great intro on original ZKP protocols.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Zero Knowledge Proofs</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.tml.tkk.fi/Opinnot/Tik-110.501/1995/zeroknowledge.html\">Zero Knowledge Protocols and Small Systems</a> - A good intro into Zero knowledge protocols.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Key Management</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/SpecialPublications/NIST.SP.800-57pt1r4.pdf\">Recommendation for Key Management – Part 1: General</a> - Methodologically very relevant document on goals and procedures of key management.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h4>Math</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.cse.iitk.ac.in/users/manindra/algebra/primality_v6.pdf\">PRIMES is in P</a> - Unconditional deterministic polynomial-time algorithm that determines whether an input number is prime or composite.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h3>Books</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://crypto.stanford.edu/~dabo/cryptobook/\">A Graduate Course in Applied Cryptography</a> - By Dan Boneh and Victor Shoup. A well-balanced introductory course into cryptography, a bit of cryptoanalysis and cryptography-related security.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h3>Books</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.esat.kuleuven.be/cosic/publications/thesis-16.pdf\">Analysis and design of cryptographic hash functions, MAC algorithms and block ciphers</a> - Broad overview of design and cryptoanalysis of various ciphers and hash functions, by Bart Van Rompay.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h3>Books</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.cryptool.org/en/ctp-documentation/ctbook\">CrypTool book</a> - Predominantly mathematically oriented information on learning, using and experimenting cryptographic procedures.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-11-28T20:15:10.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"pFarb/awesome-crypto-papers","categoryHTML":"<h2>The list</h2><h3>Books</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://cacr.uwaterloo.ca/hac/\">Handbook of Applied Cryptography</a> - By Alfred J. Menezes, Paul C. van Oorschot and Scott A. Vanstone.